comment._content: I'd say the trees and barrage balloon in the background it's some where in the Pacific Northwest during WWII, probably Washington State.

comment.author: 63500750@N06
comment._content: This shows a Douglas O-38F and North American O-47. The O-47 cowling has an ace of spades with a dagger through it, the long-time symbol of the Washington Air National Guard.

comment.author: 76863906@N02
comment._content: The 116th Observation Squadron at Fort Lewis / Gray Field flew these as trainer aircraft in 1942 and after they were passed along to the Washington NG.  This looks like other photos of Gray Field, but most of the airfields up there looked just like this.
